-- Russia May Ban Alcohol Advertising on Internet, Vedomosti Says
-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 2012-06-08T05:00:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-08/russia-may-ban-alcohol-advertising-on-internet-vedomosti-says.html
Russia may prohibit the advertising
of alcoholic drinks on the Internet,  Vedomosti  reported, citing
Igor Rudensky, the chairman of a state duma committee.  The panel will decide today whether to recommend adoption
of an alcohol advertising bill, the newspaper said. If the
measure is passed, such advertising will be outlawed from July
23 on the Internet, on television and radio and on the first and
last pages of printed media, according to the report.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Frank Connelly at 
 fconnelly@bloomberg.net  